        <num>36-82-40</num>
        <content>
          <p>The holder of any outstanding bond or bonds of any county, municipality, or political subdivision in this state issued subsequently to the adoption of the Constitution of 1877, the validating of which is not otherwise provided for by Code Sections 36-82-1 through 36-82-6 and Part 1 of this article, shall have the right to have the same validated in the manner provided in this part.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1908, p. 72, ยง 1; Civil Code 1910, ยง 453; Code 1933, ยง 87-401.)</p>
